,"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%86%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be decorated, to be adorned, to dress up, to groom oneself, to groom, to spruce, to be beautified, to bedeck oneself, to be bedecked, to adorn oneself, to powder one’s nose","examples":[{"text":"حَتَّىٰ إِذَا أَخَذَتِ ٱلْأَرْضُ زُخْرُفَهَا وَٱزَّيَّنَتْ وَظَنَّ أَهْلُهَا أَنَّهُمْ قَادِرُونَ عَلَيْهَا أَتَاهَا أَمْرُنَا"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shave, to get a shave"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَزَيَّنَ (tazayyana) (form V)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18538","headword_ar":"تزيّن","root":"zyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AizodaAna","text_ar":"اِزْدَانَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) the latter of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaEala","text_ar":"اِفْتَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aizotayana","text_ar":"اِزْتَيَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AizotaAna","text_ar":"اِزْتَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (S,) quasi-pass. verbs, [the former of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zay~anahu","text_ar":"زَيَّنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAnahu","text_ar":"زَانَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (K,) signify the same; (S;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, adorned, ornamented, decorated, decked, bedecked, garnished, embel-lished, beautified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"graced;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aiz~ay~ana","text_ar":"اِزَّيَّنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * K,) [a variation of the first, being] originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazay~ana","text_ar":"تَزَيَّنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"being made quiescent, and incorporated into the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being prefixed in order that the inception may be perfect; (S, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AzyAn~","text_ar":"ازيانّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Azyn~","text_ar":"ازينّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) One says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azoyanati","text_ar":"اَزْيَنَتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDu biEu$obihaA","text_ar":"الاَرْضُ بِعُشْبِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[perhaps a mistranscription for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aizoyan~ati","text_ar":"اِزْيَنَّتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land, became adorned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by, its herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aiz~ay~anat","text_ar":"اِزَّيَّنَت"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazay~anat","text_ar":"تَزَيَّنَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as expl. above]; (S;) and some, in the Kur x. 25, read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazay~anat","text_ar":"تَزَيَّنَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and some, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AzyAn~t","text_ar":"ازيانّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd.) And they said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA TalaEati Aljabohapu","text_ar":"اـِذَا طَلَعَتِ الجَبْهَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazay~anati Aln~axolapu","text_ar":"تَزَيَّنَتِ النَّخْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljbhp","text_ar":"الجبهة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the Tenth Mansion of the Moon)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rises aurorally, the palm-tree becomes garnished"},{"kind":"text","text":"with ripening dates: that Mansion thus rose in central Arabia, about the commencement of the era of the Flight, on the 12th of August, O. S; and in that region, at, or soon after, that period, the dates begin to ripen]. (TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tzy~n","text_ar":"تزيّن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of language, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was embellished, dressed up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trimmed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of an action &c., as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was embellished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dressed up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a person, by another man, and, more commonly, by the Devil.] ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tzy~n","text_ar":"تزيّن"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He adorned, ornamented, decorated, decked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tzy~n biAlbaATili","text_ar":"تزيّن بِالبَاطِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He invested himself with that which did not belong to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$bE","text_ar":"شبع"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AA%D8%B2%D9%8A%D9%86/","headword_ar":"تَزَيُّن","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_48","lexicon_en":"Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)","lexicon_ar":"موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=127959#c0f1c3","body_html":"تَزَيُّن<br>من (ز ي ن) التَّحَسُّن والتَّجَمُّل."}]}}